    "node_type": "recovery_modality",
    "version": "1.0",
    "name": "Heat Therapy / Sauna",
    "mechanism": "Induces mild thermic stress, triggering the release of Heat Shock Proteins (HSPs). HSPs act as molecular chaperones to refold damaged proteins inside cells. Also induces massive vasodilation, increasing blood flow and nutrient delivery to skin and muscles.",
